transpiler module¶

Handles parsing parsing an XML File and writing that to python using cupy. Entrypoint is transpile(xml_file_path)

transpiler.find_uniq_tag(tag_name, tree)¶

Finds uniq tag within tree. Raises error if none found or not unique.

Args:

tag_name (str): the Tag name to search for. tree (xml.etree.ElementTree): The tree to search through.

Returns:

xml.etree.ElementTree.Element

transpiler.print_tags(element)¶

Takes in single element and prints its child tags

transpiler.print_uniq_attrs(root)¶

Prints the Set of children attributes, takes in element, returns nothing

transpiler.print_uniq_tags(root)¶

Prints the Set of children tags, takes in element, returns nothing

transpiler.print_xml_structure(element, level=0)¶

Util: Print the xml structure 2 levels deep. Takes in element and level to start at. Returns nothing

transpiler.transpile(xml_file_path)¶

Entry point into the transpiling part, takes in a file path writes to a file in ./.generated

transpiler.transpile_constants(constants_root)¶
